    "is_free": true,
    "description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1811440/extras/6cc5005f22e375bf29a633003baa066e.avif?t=1762263278\" width=576 height=144 /></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>– How to break a city –</strong></h2>In 1923, <i>Ionia</i> sends three of their agents to an <strong>independent</strong> city state. Their mission is as follows: <strong>bribe</strong>, <strong>bully</strong>, <strong>blackmail</strong>. Whatever it takes, <i>Trachi</i> either swallows – or chokes on our terms.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong> – How to set it free –</strong></h2>It's grim news for about 40,000 residents, if weren't for a group of <strong>four defectors</strong>. Supported by a group of domestic <strong>liberators</strong> / terrorists, neither party is inclined to let the city go.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>– Fictional People –</strong></h2>With more than <strong>60 areas</strong>, <strong>19 characters</strong> and <strong>9000 lines of dialogue</strong>, <strong>AUTONOMY</strong> puts the spotlight on the power of <strong>micro-politics</strong>. It's a love-letter to narratives with uncompromising <strong>authenticity</strong> – because reality is complex at heart.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>– Fictional History –</strong></h2>Including flashbacks and flashforwards, the <strong>story</strong> spans more than <strong>ten years</strong>. One day a <strong>prisoner</strong> is shot, afterwards a <strong>girl</strong> dies to a firing squad. All of that and more, converging on a three day trip to the most important <strong>city</strong> in the world.",
